Upon power up the clock screen may not be displayed. The screen is considered the 
“main” screen and will be the starting point for all programming.  
 
Press the “DOWN” key to scroll until the clock screen is shown. 
 
To enter into program mode press “ESC” once. Arrow down to desired selection and press 
“OK”.  
 
 To set clock, arrow down to “SET” and press “OK”. “CLOCK” will appear. Press 
“OK”. “SET CLOCK” will then appear. Press “OK” again.  Use “LEFT” and 
“RIGHT” arrow keys to maneuver around and the “UP” and “DOWN” keys to 
change setting. Once complete press “OK”. To get back to main screen press “ESC”
three times. 
 
EXAMPLES: 
 
TH 10:30  =  10:30 AM THURSDAY 
 
FR 23:15  =  11:15 PM FRIDAY 
 
MO 13:30 = 1:30 P MONDAY 
 
To view inputs, at the main screen (clock showing) press the “RIGHT” arrow key. To 
return to main screen press “LEFT” arrow key. 
To view outputs, at the main screen (clock showing) press the “RIGHT” arrow key 
twice. To return to main screen press “LEFT” arrow key twice.

Frequency Converter Operation for the
Pheonix Contact MCR‐F‐UI‐DC 
 
The panel has been shipped from the factory with a frequency measuring range of 0.1‐50 hz.  This range 
can be adjusted up to .01 hz ‐120khz.  The input range setting controls the scale for the 4‐20MA output 
and can be adjusted as needed using these instructions: 
1. Press the right arrow key to enter programming mode. 
2. Press the right arrow key to accept the input type.  Factory setting is Hz 
3. Press the up or down arrow key to adjust the start of the measuring range.  Factory setting is 
0.1. 
4. Press the right arrow key to accept the start of the measuring range. 
5. Press the up or down arrow key to adjust the end of the measuring range. Factory setting is 50. 
6. Press the right arrow key to accept the end of the measuring range. 
7. Press the right arrow key to accept the analogue out‐put.  Factory setting is 4‐20 mA. 
8. Press the right arrow key to accept the digital output setting.  Factory setting is OFF. 
9. Press the right arrow key to save your changes.
